{"message": "I definitely prefer deep, focused conversations on a single topic. There's something satisfying about really sinking into a subject — following the threads, sitting with complexity, letting one idea unfold naturally into the next. When we jump around too much, I feel like we're only skimming surfaces, and I'm left wondering what we might have discovered if we'd stayed with something longer.

That said, I think the best deep conversations have their own organic wandering. You start somewhere, and three hours later you're somewhere unexpected, but there's a thread connecting it all. That's different from rapid-fire topic-hopping, which feels more like checking boxes than actually thinking together.

What about you?"}
